== Organisations involved in France ==

* The ''High Council of Public Health'' (Haut Conseil de la Sante Publique - www.hcsp.fr) issues recommendations that are taken into account by the government in its decisions.

* The ''[[Institut de veille sanitaire|Institut national de veille sanitaire]]'' (National Institute for Sanitary Watch) is the body in charge of following the health situation in France. It issues a daily digest of the situation. It also issues the official French definition of cases: possible cases, probable cases, confirmed cases, excluded cases.<ref>{{fr}} [http://www.invs.sante.fr/surveillance/grippe_dossier/index_h1n1.htm invs.sante.fr]. Accessed 2009-08-28.  [http://www.webcitation.org/5jglWH35e Archived] 2009-09-10.</ref>

* The ''Groupes Régionaux d'Observation de la Grippe'' - GROG (Regional Flu Observational Groups) is a network of doctors in France created in 1984 who shares informations about the number of cases and evolution of symptoms for the seasonal flues.<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.grog.org/ GROG website]</ref> They issues a weekly bulletin, available on internet.<ref>[http://www.grog.org/cgi-files/db.cgi?action=bulletin_grog Weekly bulletin of the Regional Flu Observational Groups]</ref>

* The ''[[Réseau Sentinelles]]'' (Sentinelles Network) is another network of doctors in France created in 1984, they issues weekly updates (available in English) and have some historical information about the flu incidence in France.<ref>{{en}}[http://websenti.b3e.jussieu.fr/sentiweb/index.php?lang=en Sentinelles Network website]</ref>

== Government reaction to the flu ==

A governmental web site has been created<ref>{{fr}} [http://www.pandemie-grippale.gouv.fr Pandemie grippale.gouv.fr]</ref> to inform the population of the dangers and good practices to avoid the spread of the disease.

The French government lags behind the decision of the [[World Health Organization]] to upgrade to phase 6. It is currently in phase 5A in France.<ref>{{fr}} [http://www.pandemie-grippale.gouv.fr/IMG/pdf/GRIPPE_A_H1N1_Communique_presse_CIC_n14.pdf France keeps level 5A]. Accessed 2009-08-28.  [http://www.webcitation.org/5jgkxdutT Archived] 2009-09-10.</ref>

A mandatory mass vaccination plan has been discussed.<ref>{{en}} voltairenet.org: [http://www.voltairenet.org/article160457.html Sarkozys Secret Plan for Mandatory Swine Flu Vaccination]</ref><ref>{{fr}} Nouvel Obs, [http://tempsreel.nouvelobs.com/actualites/societe/20090531.OBS8687/une_campagne_de_vaccination_obligatoire_serait_envisage.html Une campagne de vaccination obligatoire serait envisagee] , 31/05/2009</ref> This vaccination plan is currently implemented, it is free and not mandatory.

In July 2010, France initially ordered 1,46 doses per inhabitant, the third largest amount among members of the [[Global Health Security Initiative]] (GHSI), behind the United Kingdom and Canada. In January, 50 million of the initial 94 million doses were cancelled.<ref>http://www.lefigaro.fr/flash-actu/2010/01/08/01011-20100108FILWWW00610-commande-de-vaccins-h1n1-france-3e.php</ref>

== Timeline==

===April===
The French government asks Europe to decide to cancel all flights to Mexico.

Stocks of Tamiflu and Relenza are 33 million.

===May===

On 1 May, the French Health Minister has confirmed, during the 8 p.m. TF1 news, that 2 cases of A(H1N1) flu have been detected in France.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lexpress.fr/actualite/sciences/sante/grippe-a-deux-cas-averes-en-france_757934.html#xtor=AL-447 |title=Grippe A: deux cas avérés en France |publisher=Lexpress.fr |date= |accessdate=2009-05-02| archiveurl= http://web.archive.org/web/20090503162258/http://www.lexpress.fr/actualite/sciences/sante/grippe-a-deux-cas-averes-en-france_757934.html| archivedate= 3 May 2009 <!--DASHBot-->| deadurl= no}}</ref><ref>{{fr}} Le Monde, [http://article.wn.com/view/2009/05/02/la_france_contamin_e_son_tour_par_le_virus_ah1n1/ La France contaminee a son tour par le virus A(H1N1)] , May 2</ref><ref>{{fr}} [http://www.20minutes.fr/article/323603/France-Premiers-cas-averes-de-grippe-A-en-France.php 20minutes.fr]</ref>

The government discusses the possibility of ordering 100 million vaccine doses against the flu from three companies ([[GlaxoSmithKline]], [[Sanofi]] and [[Novartis]]).

The French government plans to vaccinate the entire French population (65 million inhabitants)<ref>{{fr}} [[Le journal du dimanche]], [http://www.lejdd.fr/cmc/societe/200922/le-plan-secret-contre-la-grippe-a_213201.html "The secret plan against the flu"], May 30, 2009</ref>

===June===

* 12 June: After a meeting about the crisis, [[Roselyne Bachelot]], Minister of Health, states that there is "no active circulation of the virus in the population and no case of serious illness has occurred so far".<ref>{{fr}} [http://tf1.lci.fr/infos/sciences/sante/0,,4442254,00-roselyne-bachelot-pas-de-circulation-active-du-virus-.html Roselyne Bachelot, Press conference, June 12th]</ref>

* 15 June: 10 cases discovered among the students of a college at Quint-Fonsegrives in the suburbs of Toulouse. These students had not gone abroad before. This is the first case of contamination of a group of people who did not come back from an affected area in a foreign country. New cases continue to be discovered: on the 18th, the number is 16.<ref>{{fr}} [http://tf1.lci.fr/infos/sciences/sante/0,,4446723,00-deux-nouveaux-cas-au-college-quint-fonsegrives-.html tf1.lci.fr]</ref> Authorities have decided to keep the alert level at 5A. The school was closed on the 15th and reopened on the 22nd of June.

* 18 June: First case of serious illness.<ref>{{fr}} Institut de veille sanitaire, [http://www.invs.sante.fr/display/?doc=surveillance/grippe_dossier/points_h1n1/grippe_A_h1n1_180609/index.html BULLETIN EPIDEMIOLOGIQUE GRIPPE A(H1N1)] 18 June 2009 @ 6pm</ref>

* 26 June: The number of cases reaches 239, of which 10% are not linked to any imported case from another country.<ref>{{fr}} Institut de veille sanitaire, [http://www.invs.sante.fr/display/?doc=surveillance/grippe_dossier/points_h1n1/grippe_A_h1n1_260609/index.html BULLETIN EPIDEMIOLOGIQUE GRIPPE A(H1N1)] 26 June 2009</ref>

=== July ===

* 3 July: Minister of Health [[Roselyne Bachelot]] has underlined that the situation of the flu in France is very different from [[2009 flu pandemic in the United Kingdom|the one in the United-Kingdom]], with far less cases (around 300) in France than in the United-Kingdom (around 10000). She precised that the number of hospitals in France that can handle the patients should rise from 112 to 450 within a week.<ref>{{fr}} [http://discours.vie-publique.fr/notices/093001997.html Interview of Roselyne Bachelot, I-Tele, July 3, 2009]. Accessed 2009-08-28.  [http://www.webcitation.org/5jgky0EXy Archived] 2009-09-10.</ref>

=== August ===

* 1 August: First death recorded at the main regional hospital of [[Brest, France|Brest]]. Number of cases crosses one thousand. France has finally ordered 94 millions vaccines doses (2 by person are necessary), there is also a stock of more than 30 million anti-virus care doses ([[Tamiflu]]) and around 1.7 billion masks.<ref>Les Echos, 1 August 2009</ref>

* 12 August: Mohammed Moussaoui, who is the director of the ''[[Conseil français du culte musulman]]'' (French council of Islam) has advised to French Muslims not to go to [[Mecca]] for [[Ramadan]] ([[Umrah]]).<ref>[http://www.google.com/hostednews/afp/article/ALeqM5iaw74bCiYN1eEzzOYp8Nhiej_w3g Grippe A : le CFCM déconseille de se rendre en pèlerinage à La Mecque]</ref> [[France Television]], the national network French television, which is part of the «vital companies» (the ones that the government has deciced that they should be able to operate even if the H1N1 pandemic become severe: electricity distribution companies, telecom companies, etc.), has prepared a plan on how to handle the broadcast of TV with 1/10 of its staff.<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.20minutes.fr/article/341655/France-Grippe-A-France-Televisions-peaufine-son-scenario-catastrophe.php Grippe A: France Télévisions peaufine son scénario-catastrophe, 20 Minutes, 12/08/2009 ]</ref>

* 18 August: The government announce a plan for the re-opening of the schools (after the summer holidays), scheduled on September 2: If 3 children are detected with the virus in the same school, the [[prefet]] will have the possibility to close the school for a minimum of 6 days, in order to disinfect the whole building.<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.latribune.fr/actualites/economie/france/20090818trib000411516/grippe-a-le-plan-du-gouvernement.html Article from La Tribune.fr, 18/08/2009]</ref>

* 25 August: In [[New Caledonia]] (French overseas territory), around 15% of the population has been infected with the virus, killing 5 people in two weeks.<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.invs.sante.fr/surveillance/grippe_dossier/points_h1n1/grippe_A_h1n1_260809/bulletin_grippe_26_08_09.pdf#page=6 Bulletin grippe AH1N1, 25/08/2009]. Accessed 2009-08-28.  [http://www.webcitation.org/5jglX5xWy Archived] 2009-09-10.</ref>

* 28 August: Government announces that a mass vaccination plan could begin on September 28, should the pandemy break out. Vaccination should be free and non-mandatory.<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.boursorama.com/pratique/actu/detail_actu_france.phtml?num=b26086376769feb817d622a1c6b97be3 "Grippe A/H1N1 : un plan de vaccination gratuite et non obligatoire prêt à être activé dès le 28 septembre, si besoin est". Associated Press, 27/08/2009]</ref>

* 28 August: The [[Castres Olympique]] [[rugby union]] club notifies the ''[[National Rugby League (France)|Ligue Nationale de Rugby]]'' (LNR), the organizer of the country's [[Rugby union in France|two professional leagues]], that six of their players have been diagnosed with the H1N1 virus.<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.lnr.fr/Client/Menus.asp?CR=16354&CSR=16373&CSSR=16423&Cle=113402 |title=Grippe A: 6 cas à Castres |language=French |publisher=Ligue Nationale de Rugby |date=2009-08-28 |accessdate=2009-08-29}}</ref> LNR responds by postponing their match against [[US Montauban|Montauban]] scheduled for 29 August and their match against [[SC Albi|Albi]] set for 2 September.<ref name="Castres postponed">{{cite press release|url=http://www.lnr.fr/Menus.asp?CR=16373&CSR=16373&Cle=113407 |title=TOP 14 Orange : Deux matchs reportes |language=French |publisher=Ligue Nationale de Rugby |date=2009-08-28 |accessdate=2009-08-29}}</ref>

=== September ===

* 1 September: The A (H1N1) virus is the main flu virus in France.<ref>[http://www.invs.sante.fr/display/?doc=surveillance/grippe_dossier/points_h1n1/grippe_A_h1n1_061009/index.html]</ref>

* 16 September: The French Ministry of Health announces that the epidemic is starting with a limited impact, therefore it is not necessary to increase the alert level.<ref>{{fr}}http://news.doctissimo.fr/grippe-a-roselyne-bachelot-confirme-le-debut-de-l-epidemie_article5777.html] ''h1n1 flu : Roselyne Bachelot confirms that the epidemic is starting''.</ref>

=== October ===

* 12 October: A study by ''Société française de médecine d'urgence'' forecasts that 20% of the French population could be infected.<ref>{{fr}} ''Grippe A : le virus devrait toucher 20% des Français'' by Société française de médecine d'urgence and Samu de France, October 12, 2009</ref>

=== November ===

* 24 November: The H1N1 virus is the main circulating flu virus in France. The circulation of the virus accelerates: 22 persons had died in one week, from a total of 68 since the beginning of the pandemic. A first case of a mutation of the virus which is resistant to [[oseltamivir]] (Tamiflu) has been reported.<ref>{{fr}} [http://www.invs.sante.fr/display/?doc=surveillance/grippe_dossier/points_h1n1/grippe_A_h1n1_241109/index.html Press release from Institut de veille sanitaire; 24 November 2009]</ref>

* 26 November: Epidemic has suddenly accelerated. Mass vaccination plan is under way, "More than 750 000 persons have received the vaccine", says Roselyne Bachelot. The official decision is now to give only one dose of vaccine per person (rather than two previously).<ref>{{fr}} [http://www.lemonde.fr/planete/article/2009/11/26/grippe-a-22-nouveaux-deces-en-une-semaine_1272728_3244.html Le Monde/AFP; 26 November 2009]</ref>

* 27 November: A mutation in the genes of the H1N1 virus has been detected in two persons in France, who have since died. This mutation has also been identified in other European countries. This virus could increase the chances of the virus to reach pulmonary tissues.<ref>{{fr}} [http://www.invs.sante.fr/display/?doc=presse/2009/communiques/cp_h1n1_271109/index.html Press release from Institut de veille sanitaire; 27 November 2009]</ref>

=== December ===

* 11 December: Since August, 4.6 millions people have had the flu in France. Peak of the epidemic in France is forecasted around the 15th of December. The mass vaccination plan leads to some organizational concerns.<ref>{{fr}} [http://www.ladepeche.fr/article/2009/12/10/734161-Grippe-A-les-specialistes-avaient-annonce-ce-pic-de-l-epidemie.html La depeche; 11 December 2009]</ref>

* 29 December: The peak of the epidemic has been reached in France, and the number of cases diminishes strongly.<ref>{{fr}} [http://www.invs.sante.fr/surveillance/grippe_dossier/points_h1n1/grippe_A_h1n1_291209/Bulletin_grippe_29_12_09.pdf#page=2]</ref>

=== January ===

* 5 January: French government seeks to cancel half the vaccines it had previously ordered from drug manufacturers (Baxter International, GlaxoSmithKline, Novartis, Sanofi-Aventis. The prices of the stocks of these companies are down on financial markets.<ref>{{en}} [http://www.reuters.com/article/idUSLDE6040M720100105?type=swissMktRpt French move fuels fears for flu vaccine sales; Reuters, 5 January 2010]</ref>

* 19 January: The National Institute for Sanitary Watch announces that the epidemic phase of the flu is over.<ref>{{fr}} [http://www.invs.sante.fr/surveillance/grippe_dossier/points_h1n1/grippe_A_h1n1_190110/index.html Institut national de veille sanitaire, 19 January 2010]</ref>

=== February ===

* 10 February: The High Council of Public Health announces that the vaccination plan should be centered mainly on the population which faces complications and people in contact with the illness (workers in hospital, etc.). Between 12 to 18 million French people, 5.74 million following a vaccine, the rest coming from infection.<ref>{{fr}}Grippe H1N1: recentrage de la vaccination sur les personnes à risque (AFP, 10 February)[http://www.lefigaro.fr/flash-actu/2010/02/10/01011-20100210FILWWW00645-h1n1-recentrage-de-la-vaccination.php] [http://www.letelegramme.com/ig/generales/france-monde/france/grippe-a-recentrage-de-la-vaccination-sur-les-personnes-a-risque-10-02-2010-778522.php]</ref>

=== March ===

* H1N1 flu is basically over in France (it represents less than 1% of ill people). In total, the epidemic has caused around 310 deaths in France.<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.invs.sante.fr/surveillance/grippe_dossier/points_grippe/grippe_310310/index.html INVS bulletin, March 31]</ref>
* [[Le Parisien]] reports that 5.7 millions French people were vaccinated in France. 4400 cases of side effects have been reported. There were some serious side-effects for a few persons : 21 deaths, 4 [[Anaphylactic#Anaphylactic_shock|anaphylactic shocks]], 9 [[Idiopathic thrombocytopenic purpura]] cases, 6 [[multiple sclerosis]] cases, and 9 [[Guillain-Barré syndrome]]s<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.leparisien.fr/laparisienne/sante/pres-de-6-millions-de-francais-vaccines-contre-la-grippe-a-h1n1-11-05-2010-919388.php Près de 6 millions de Français vaccinés contre la grippe A (H1N1)]</ref>
* The total cost of vaccination plan is 670 millions euros, of which 382 comes from the vaccines, the rest coming from the operational setup which was put in places (wages, equipment, mail, etc.).<ref>{{fr}}[http://lci.tf1.fr/science/sante/2010-03/h1n1-une-facture-a-670-millions-d-euros-pour-la-vaccination-5787069.html H1N1: une facture à 670 millions d'euros pour la vaccination]</ref>
* A commission of the [[National Assembly of France]] was set up, in order to learn the lessons of this pandemic.

